From 39325f2f564b82706fb18c78860b70a23f4e2937 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yding@qventus.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 17:45:35 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] oauth2: send PKCE code_challenge for OIDC login sources

When Gitea acts as an OIDC client (login source), it never sent a PKCE
code_challenge on the authorization request, so identity providers that require
PKCE (e.g. a django-oauth-toolkit provider with PKCE_REQUIRED) rejected sign-in
(go-gitea/gitea#34747, go-gitea/gitea#21376).

Generate a per-request S256 verifier in Callout, stash it in the user session,
and append code_challenge to the authorization redirect; on the callback inject
the stored code_verifier so goth forwards it to the token exchange. Gated to the
openidConnect provider via a provider SupportsPKCE() capability; no settings,
schema, or dependency changes (golang.org/x/oauth2 ships the helpers).

Ported onto Gitea v1.26.2 for Artea's gitea/patches queue (ADR-0009); on a path
to deletion once merged upstream.

Assisted-by: Claude Code:claude-opus-4-8[1m]
